          <Base:Description type="brief">
             polished smoke grey and ebony fireplace
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="examine">
             Jutting from the northeast corner of the sitting room, and made of polished, smoke grey stone and ebony, is a massive fireplace. It has a wide mouth with an arched top and is flanked on either side by carved stone trees. The green mahogany mantel above is a foot deep and ends above the columns on either side of the hearth. Inside the fireplace is an iron rack holding a small pile of logs above a grating on the floor of the fireplace. The chimney continues above the fireplace to the floors above. A small iron stand is to the left of the fireplace, to hold fireplace tools.{? | $(this.trait:lit) |The fireplace is currently lit.}
          </Base:Description>
